name: Amira Elfeky
summary: Amira Lynne Elfeky is an American-Egyptian singer/songwriter based out of Los Angeles, California. Amira, a Connecticut native, met producer/multi-instrumentalist, Brandon Iljas in 2017 by posting a “drummer wanted” ad. Together, they have crafted several tracks in Brandon’s DIY bedroom studio in San Francisco. Their production style combines the synth and guitar tones of lo-fi bedroom pop with modern vocals and boom bap style drums. Having dealt with anxiety and depression for most of her life, Amira sought solace in music. Read more on Last.fm

name: Caskets
summary: Caskets, formed in 2018 under the name Captives, is a British post-hardcore band from Leeds, England. The band was founded by bassist Christopher McIntosh, who played rhythm guitar at the time, Benji Wilson (lead guitar) and bassist Lee Horner, who together left their previous project Faultlines to pursue new projects. The band was completed with James Lazenby (drums) and Matthew Flood (vocals). Flood had previously played guitar and sang in the pop punk band Silhouettes. Read more on Last.fm

name: Rage Against The Machine
summary: Rage Against the Machine were an American rock band from Los Angeles, California. Formed in 1991, the group consisted of vocalist Zack de la Rocha, bassist and backing vocalist Tim Commerford, guitarist Tom Morello, and drummer Brad Wilk. Their songs express revolutionary left-wing political views. As of 2010, they had sold over 16 million records worldwide. In 2023, the band was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame. Rage Against the Machine released its eponymous debut album in 1992 to commercial and critical success Read more on Last.fm
